      <div class="poem">
        <h1>nightstand</h1>
          <h2>by Matthew Stokdyk</h2>
            <p>He liked Durex condoms,<br />
            and I liked Trojan;<br />
            we kept both in the drawer.<br /><br />
            Later, she liked none,<br />
            but I kept them there<br />
            in case we came to our senses.</p>
            <div class="origPub"><p>Originally published in <!-- double check the title on the physical copy, because i know it went through revisions --><span style="font-style:italic">Anatomy of a Nightstand</span>, a zine put together <a href="http://yusiliu.digital.brynmawr.edu/index.html" class="plainLink">by Yusi Liu</a> for <a href="https://www.littlebookwi.com/place-spaces-edition-3" class="plainLink">the Spring 2021 edition of the Little Book Project in Madison.</a></p></div>
      </div>
